# Orion — local HTTPS reverse proxy
#
# Serves Orion at a friendly hostname instead of localhost:5176 / :3000.
#
# On this machine Caddy runs as a root Homebrew service and its real config is
# /opt/homebrew/etc/Caddyfile (which also fronts aether-dev + website-dev). This
# file is the Orion-specific block, kept in-repo for documentation; it is copied
# into the system Caddyfile. See README "Local access" for setup.
#
#   1. Add to /etc/hosts:    127.0.0.1 orion.hunt
#   2. Append the block below to /opt/homebrew/etc/Caddyfile
#   3. Restart:              sudo /opt/homebrew/bin/brew services restart caddy
#   4. Visit:                https://orion.hunt
#
# Dev points at Vite (:5176), which itself proxies /api -> the Bun API (:3000).
# `tls internal` is required because orion.hunt is not a real public domain —
# it makes Caddy issue a cert from its own local CA (already trusted on this Mac).
# Vite must also list "orion.hunt" in server.allowedHosts (see web/vite.config.js).
#
# In production the Bun server serves the built frontend from web/dist on :3000,
# so point reverse_proxy at localhost:3000 instead of :5176.

orion.hunt {
	tls internal
	reverse_proxy localhost:5176
}
